data.title: George Van Eps-Gene hackman's estranged brother?
data.text:
On Thu, 09 May 2002 19:54:38 GMT, "Rick Ross" <rick...@adelphia.net>

wrote:



Good book, I enjoyed listening to a number of players I hadn't heard

before and its got a good transcription of a Jack Wilkins tune from

his Trio Art album. By the way, Hackman (great acator) is Gene

Hackman's real last name, was born in IL and Van Eps (real name) was

born in New Jersey some 13 years earlier. r/rob taft

On Fri, 10 May 2002 00:28:32 GMT, "Rick Ross" <rick...@adelphia.net>

wrote:



No Jack Zucker in the Mel Bay book. But I had to take a look a the

book and a pic of gene hackman. I can see where one could see a

resemblance in the photo in the Mel Bay book, Some similar features.

Maybe if I squint harder. r/rob

<rain...@optonline.net> wrote:

>Joe Torre and Ernest Borgnine?

>

Back in 1977, Chic Magazine ran a one page photo feature with these

pairs:

Bob Dylan - Bette Midler

James Baldwin - Nina Simone

John Denver - Margaret Mead

Lyndon Johnson - Golda Meir

Rubin "Hurricane" Carter - Isaac Hayes

Jack London- Ted Kennedy

Charles Aznavour - Gay Talese

Gerald Ford - Joe Palooka

Then there was a portrait that the New York Times ran of Richard Nixon

in his later years. My jaw dropped - the man had turned into Mao

Tse-tung!
